{"title":"Men’s Tour de Suisse 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-suisse-preview","date":1717606338000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-suisse-preview\">Men’s Tour de Suisse 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>The men’s Tour de Suisse, the final warm-up race before the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a>, starts on Sunday 9th June with a prologue around Vaduz and finishes the following Sunday, 16th June, in Villars-sur-Ollion, less than two weeks before the Tour starts in Florence, Italy. The eight-stage race has, together with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/criterium-du-dauphine-preview\" target=\"_blank\">Critérium du Dauphiné</a>, long been where Tour hopefuls test their legs before the biggest race of the season. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year’s Tour de Suisse was won by Mattias Skjelmose (Lidl-Trek) ahead of Juan Ayuso (UAE Team Emriates) and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a> (Soudal-QuickStep). However, the race was marred by tragedy, as 26-year-old Swiss rider <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2023-pro-cycling-tour-de-suisse\" target=\"_blank\">Gino Mäder died after a crash on a descent on Stage 5</a>. Stage 6 was then neutralised before racing resumed on Stage 7, when winner Evenepoel dedicated his victory on the day to Mäder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 edition will honour Mäder, retiring his race number (44) and creating a new #rideforGino prize given to the first rider to cross the highest point of the race. A memorial ride will also take place covering the route of the final stage.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gotthard-pass-cycling\">Tunisia Diaries: Cycling up the Gotthard Pass with 20kg of luggage</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/criterium-du-dauphine-preview\">Critérium du Dauphiné 2024: Route, TV guide and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/roger-de-vlaeminck-tour-de-suisse\">Pro history: Roger De Vlaeminck dominates the 1975 Tour de Suisse</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/switzerland-aigle-cycling\">Big Ride: Switzerland’s seat of power</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2024: Route, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Suisse 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Ride-for-Gino-Mader-the-2023-Tour-de-Suisse-by-Michael-Steele-via-Getty-Images-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Michael Steele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dates:</strong> 9th-16th June 2024</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Start:</strong> Vaduz</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Finish:</strong> Villars-sur-Ollon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stages:</strong> Eight</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>UK television coverage:</strong> Discovery+</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Most wins:</strong> Pasquale Fornara (four)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>2023 winner:</strong> Mattias Skjelmose (Lidl-Trek)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Suisse 2024: The route</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"687\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-970x687.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-970x687.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-300x213.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-768x544.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-120x86.png 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-750x531.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-1140x808.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map-190x136.png 190w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Tour-de-Suisse-2024-map.png 1270w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The route is once again bookended by individual time-trials, with the stages in between packed with climbs. The queen stage is currently being reorganised as the Nufenen Pass is closed due to snow.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Suisse 2024: Stage-by-stage preview</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Sunday 9th June, Vaduz – Vaduz, 4.8km, ITT</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23-970x495.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23-970x495.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23-300x153.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23-768x392.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23-750x383.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23-1140x581.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-12.30.23.png 1294w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Pancake flat, as usual. Last year’s opener was won by Stefan Küng (Groupama-FDJ) ahead of Evenepoel and Wout van Aert.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Monday 10th June, Vaduz – Regensdorf, 177.2km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"486\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-970x486.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-970x486.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-300x150.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-768x385.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-360x180.png 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-750x376.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11-1140x572.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.25.11.png 1304w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One for the sprinters, which says a lot about the testing nature of the Tour de Suisse courses. Once they’re over the Category 2 climbs, riders hit a Category 3 with just under 10km to the finish to thin out the pack before the line. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Tuesday 11th June, Steinmaur – Rüschlikon, 161.7km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"518\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47-970x518.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47-970x518.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47-300x160.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47-768x410.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47-750x401.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47-1140x609.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.27.47.png 1306w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plenty of time to talk at the beginning of a backloaded Stage 3, with all the climbing action coming in the last 30km before an uphill finish into Rüschlikon.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Wednesday 12th June, Rüschlikon – Passo san Gottardo, 171km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"514\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04-970x514.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04-970x514.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04-300x159.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04-768x407.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04-750x397.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04-1140x604.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.30.04.png 1280w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 3 is all but pan flat before an all-important slog up the famous <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gotthard-pass-cycling\">Gotthardpass</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Thursday 13th June, Ambrì – Carì, 148.6km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"470\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22-970x470.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22-970x470.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22-300x145.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22-768x372.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22-750x363.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22-1140x552.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.32.22.png 1288w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A fierce day that will test the general classification contenders. From the Category 2 Ronco, riders will then crest the Category 1 Cari and head over the finish line for the first time, travelling out to Arbedo-Castione, looping back on themselves and finishing back on top of the Cari climb.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Friday 14th June, Locarno – Blatten, 151.4km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"484\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-970x484.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-970x484.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-300x150.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-768x383.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-360x180.png 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-750x374.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54-1140x569.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.39.54.png 1330w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This stage is currently being organised as the Nufenen Pass is closed due to snow.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7: Saturday 15th June, Villars-sur-Ollon – Villars-sur-Ollon, 118.2km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"493\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53-970x493.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53-970x493.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53-300x152.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53-768x390.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53-750x381.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53-1140x579.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/Screenshot-2024-06-05-at-13.41.53.png 1292w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A shorter but not sweeter stage, featuring a double ascent of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/switzerland-aigle-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">Col de la Croix</a> before one last summit finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 8: Sunday 16th June, Aigle – Villars-sur-Ollon, 15.7km</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"519\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-970x519.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-970x519.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-300x161.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-768x411.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-1536x822.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-2048x1096.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-750x401.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/tour-de-suisse-2024-stage-8-1140x610.png 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The 2024 Tour de Suisse ends with a time-trial as is customary, featuring almost 900m of altitude gain.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Suisse 2024: Live TV and streaming guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/2023-Tour-de-Suisse-podium-by-Tim-de-Waele-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>The Gotthard Pass is not to be missed.</figcaption><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour de Suisse will be shown throughout the week on <a href=\"https://www.discoveryplus.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> in the UK and Europe. There’s no Eurosport coverage. In the US, the racing will be shown on FloBikes and in Switzerland it is on SRF.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, has specific advice for watching cycling and costs £5.36 per month with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Live TV and streaming times</h3>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Sunday 9th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00 – 16:40 </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Monday 10th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 14:00 – 16:40</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Tuesday 11th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 14:00 – 16:40</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Wednesday 12th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 14:00 – 16:40</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Thursday 13th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 14:00 – 16:40</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Friday 14th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 13:30 – 16:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7: Saturday 15th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 13:50 – 17:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 8: Sunday 16th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 14:00 – 16:40</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Suisse 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=16&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Suisse: Previous winners</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"698\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9